arts.ttl: Leyton Orient at home after penalties win over Boreham Wood
arts.sum: Orient had eased into a two-goal lead after 49 minutes, Sonny Perkins and Dan Agyei the men on target, but the hosts hit back with goals by Tyrone Marsh and Charlie O’Connell making it 2-2 and taking the tie to extra time. “I’m relieved because the ultimate aim was to be in the draw for the second round,” said Wellens, who saw his side reduced to 10 men in extra time when Jayden Sweeney was sent off for a second bookable offence.
